## 5. Snwolley API Integration

### Agents API — Signal Explanation
**Trigger:** Every time a signal fires
**Prompt sent:**
```
You are PipSense, a trading assistant for beginner Ghanaian traders.
A signal just fired on {instrument}.
Signal type: {type} (Breakout/Sweep)
Direction: {direction} (BUY/SELL)
Entry: {entry}
Stop Loss: {sl}
TP1: {tp1}, TP2: {tp2}, TP3: {tp3}

Explain in 2-3 simple sentences why this signal fired and what it means.
Use plain English. No jargon. The reader is a complete beginner.
```
**Response:** 2–3 sentence explanation shown on signal card

---

### TTS API — Voice Announcement
**Trigger:** Signal fires (auto) or user taps voice button (manual)
**Text sent:**
```
PipSense signal. {BUY/SELL} {Gold/Bitcoin}.
{Explanation from Agents API}.
Entry at {entry}. Stop loss at {sl}.
Take profit targets: {tp1}, {tp2}, and {tp3}.
```
**Response:** WAV file played automatically in browser

